cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with regularization in the context of small sample-size learning with over-parameterized neural networks. It also involves empirical evidence across various vision benchmarks to support the claim for better generalization. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the empirical evidence is obtained across various vision benchmarks. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with neural networks and their internal representations. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks and regularization. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves a topological constraint on samples drawn from the probability measure induced in the space of internal representations.
